      "content": "but that's the thing tho, it goes deeper than just looking \"formal.\" i was reading about how certain geometric alignments in cities can actually influence the collective psyche of the people living there. like, if you trace the lines from the obelisk through the avenues, it creates this specific flow. don't you think it's suspicious that such huge amounts of money and math were spent just to make it look \"civic\"? it feels like there's a functional purpose to the shape itself, like it's designed to channel a specific type of energy or behavior from the population.",
